description: This is almost never an independent stop, being much too high-pitched, but is a rank found in mixtures. It sounds the 32nd harmonic. Its pitch is 1/4' when reinforcing the 8' harmonic series, and 1/2' when reinforcing the 16' harmonic series.
examplesDescription: No examples of Trigesima-sexta are known. Contributions welcome. All known examples of the other names are given below.
